 NIGERIAN Football Supporters Club (NFSC) have commiserated with the Federal Government over the loss of the late Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari who was the victim of the deadly Coronavirus. According to the President-General of NFSC, Rafiu Ladipo, Abba Kyari was a great loss to the football family and Nigeria as a nation. “We as a group of football supporters club hereby commiserate with the  President Muhammadu Buhari, and Nigerians over Kyari’s death. He was a man who loved and showed much interest in football. In spirit, he was always part of us as a great friend of the group. We just like to appreciate him and his death further proved that Coronavirus is ‘real,” he said. Ladipo, however, used the medium to appeal to Nigerians to abide by the rules and keep social distance in every part of their endeavours.